data.title: Nobel Prize
data.meta_description: Awards.pdf - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document provides information about several prestigious international awards, including details about their origins, categories, and notable winners. It begins with background on the Nobel Prizes, including their establishment in 1895 from Alfred Nobel's will. It then provides specifics about 2010 Nobel Prize winners in Physics, Chemistry, Literature, Peace, and Economics. The document also summarizes the Magsaysay Award, established in 1957 in memory of the former Philippines president; lists 2010 winners; and notes 2008-2009 Indian winners. It concludes with brief overviews of the Man Booker Prize, Man Booker International Prize, Commonwealth Writers' Prize, and Orange Prize for Fiction.
